Class LocalStore<V extends org.checkerframework.shaded.dataflow.analysis.AbstractValue<V>>

java.lang.Object
com.google.errorprone.dataflow.LocalStore<V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
LocalVariableValues<V>, org.checkerframework.shaded.dataflow.analysis.Store<LocalStore<V>>
public final class LocalStore<V extends org.checkerframework.shaded.dataflow.analysis.AbstractValue<V>>
extends Object
implements org.checkerframework.shaded.dataflow.analysis.Store<LocalStore<V>>, LocalVariableValues<V>
Immutable map from each local variable to its AbstractValue. Note that, while the interface is written in terms of nodes, the stored data is indexed by variable declaration, so values persist across nodes.

To derive a new instance, create a builder from an old instance. To start from scratch, call empty().

Author:
deminguyen@google.com (Demi Nguyen)

      public V valueOfLocalVariable​(org.checkerframework.shaded.dataflow.cfg.node.LocalVariableNode node, V defaultValue)
      Description copied from interface: LocalVariableValues
      Provides the nullness values of local variables (as far as they can be determined). If the nullness value cannot be definitively determined (for example, because the variable is a parameter with no assignments within the method and wasn't given an explicit initial value), defaultValue will be returned.
